comment: Event for an editing operation having ended.

variables.name: FINAL_STATE_SUCCEEDED
variables.comment: The editing operation was successful.

variables.name: FINAL_STATE_CANCELED
variables.comment: The editing operation was canceled.

variables.name: FINAL_STATE_ERROR
variables.comment: The editing operation failed due to an error.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_NONE
variables.comment: Special value representing that no error occurred.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_FAILED_RUNTIME_CHECK
variables.comment: Error code for unexpected runtime errors.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_IO_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment: Error code for non-specific errors during input/output.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_IO_NETWORK_CONNECTION_FAILED
variables.comment: Error code for network connection failures.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_IO_NETWORK_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT
variables.comment: Error code for network timeouts.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_IO_BAD_HTTP_STATUS
variables.comment: Caused by an HTTP server returning an unexpected HTTP response status code.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_IO_FILE_NOT_FOUND
variables.comment: Caused by a non-existent file.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_IO_NO_PERMISSION
variables.comment:
* Caused by lack of permission to perform an IO operation. For example, lack of permission to
     * access internet or external storage.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_IO_CLEARTEXT_NOT_PERMITTED
variables.comment:
* Caused by failing to load data via cleartext HTTP, when the app's network security
     * configuration does not permit it.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_IO_READ_POSITION_OUT_OF_RANGE
variables.comment: Caused by reading data out of the data bounds.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_DECODER_INIT_FAILED
variables.comment: Caused by a decoder initialization failure.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_DECODING_FAILED
variables.comment: Caused by a failure while trying to decode media samples.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_DECODING_FORMAT_UNSUPPORTED
variables.comment: Caused by trying to decode content whose format is not supported.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_ENCODER_INIT_FAILED
variables.comment: Caused by an encoder initialization failure.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_ENCODING_FAILED
variables.comment: Caused by a failure while trying to encode media samples.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_ENCODING_FORMAT_UNSUPPORTED
variables.comment: Caused by trying to encode content whose format is not supported.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_VIDEO_FRAME_PROCESSING_FAILED
variables.comment: Caused by a video frame processing failure.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_AUDIO_PROCESSING_FAILED
variables.comment: Caused by an audio processing failure.

variables.name: ERROR_CODE_MUXING_FAILED
variables.comment: Caused by a failure while muxing media samples.

variables.name: TIME_SINCE_CREATED_UNKNOWN
variables.comment: Special value for unknown {@linkplain #getTimeSinceCreatedMillis() time since creation}.

variables.name: PROGRESS_PERCENT_UNKNOWN
variables.comment: Special value for unknown {@linkplain #getFinalProgressPercent() final progress}.

variables.name: OPERATION_TYPE_VIDEO_TRANSCODE
variables.comment: Input video was decoded and re-encoded.

variables.name: OPERATION_TYPE_AUDIO_TRANSCODE
variables.comment: Input audio was decoded and re-encoded.

variables.name: OPERATION_TYPE_VIDEO_EDIT
variables.comment: Input video was edited.

variables.name: OPERATION_TYPE_AUDIO_EDIT
variables.comment: Input audio was edited.

variables.name: OPERATION_TYPE_VIDEO_TRANSMUX
variables.comment: Input video samples were written (muxed) directly to the output file without transcoding.

variables.name: OPERATION_TYPE_AUDIO_TRANSMUX
variables.comment: Input audio samples were written (muxed) directly to the output file without transcoding.

variables.name: OPERATION_TYPE_PAUSED
variables.comment: The editing operation was paused before it completed.

variables.name: OPERATION_TYPE_RESUMED
variables.comment: The editing operation resumed a previous (paused) operation.

methods.name: public int getFinalState()
methods.comment: Returns the state of the editing session when it ended.

methods.name: public float getFinalProgressPercent()
methods.comment:
* Returns the progress of the editing operation in percent at the moment that it ended, or
     * {@link #PROGRESS_PERCENT_UNKNOWN} if unknown.

methods.name: public int getErrorCode()
methods.comment: Returns the error code for a {@linkplain #FINAL_STATE_ERROR failed} editing session.

methods.name: public long getTimeSinceCreatedMillis()
methods.comment:
* Gets the elapsed time since creating of the editing session, in milliseconds, or {@link
     * #TIME_SINCE_CREATED_UNKNOWN} if unknown.
     *
     * @return The elapsed time since creating the editing session, in milliseconds, or {@link
     *     #TIME_SINCE_CREATED_UNKNOWN} if unknown.
     * @see LogSessionId
     * @see EditingSession

methods.name: public String getExporterName()
methods.comment:
* Returns the name of the library implementing the exporting operation, for example, a Maven
     * artifact ID like "androidx.media3.media3-transformer:1.3.0-beta01", or {@code null} if
     * unknown.

methods.name: public String getMuxerName()
methods.comment:
* Returns the name of the library implementing the media muxing operation, for example, a Maven
     * artifact ID like "androidx.media3.media3-muxer:1.3.0-beta01", or {@code null} if unknown.

methods.name: public List<MediaItemInfo> getInputMediaItemInfos()
methods.comment: Gets information about the input media items, or an empty list if unspecified.

methods.name: public MediaItemInfo getOutputMediaItemInfo()
methods.comment: Gets information about the output media item, or {@code null} if unspecified.

methods.name: public long getOperationTypes()
methods.comment: Gets a set of flags describing the types of operations performed.

methods.name: public Bundle getMetricsBundle()
methods.comment:
* Gets metrics-related information that is not supported by dedicated methods. * *

It is intended to be used for backwards compatibility by the metrics infrastructure.
